Amongst the talents in Nigeria, there are some whose talents just happen to run in the family. This week, Weekend Magazine takes a look at celebrities with famous siblings. DJ Cuppy & Temi Otedola Nigeria’s highest paid disc jokey, Florence Otedola, also known as DJ Cuppy, has an equally famous younger sister, the brain behind JTO Fashion brand, Temi. Both of them are daughters of billionaire oil mogul, Femi Otedola. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Don Jazzy & D’Prince Artiste, D’Prince younger brother to music producer, Don Jazzy whom he has to thank for his rise to stardom after he signed him to his Mo Hits Records in the mid 2000s. D’Banj and K Switch Another musical sibling duo is D’Banj and K Switch, who were also signed to Don Jazzy’s Mo Hits. Both have enjoyed flourishing careers in the music industry. Kunle and Gabriel Afolayan These two brothers have been dominating Nollywood, with Kunle doing his magic behind the camera as director and producer, and Gabriel shining on the screen in acting. MI and Jesse Jagz Perhaps two of the biggest rappers in Nigeria come from the same family. Brothers MI and Jesse Jagz, were signed to Chocolate City in 2010 and continued to soar in their various careers despite Jesse’s decision to leave Choc City. Ebony corrects controversial D’banj interview Working with Snoop Dogg  is a dream come true  – D’Banj 5 Nigerian celebs born with silver spoon Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin